commit.message: Use arc4random on macOS. Previously we were relying on /dev/urandom, which on macOS uses the Yarrow PRNG with a 160 bit security limit. New macOS systems use AES for arc4random, so it is safer to make the switch.

verification.payload:
tree c9ce0338d1b0cd94ff766ee1b04a314278a71597
parent 34f9eac0e74cf34f6fb5fd5d4e64049e680171c3

Use arc4random on macOS. Previously we were relying on /dev/urandom, which on macOS uses the Yarrow PRNG with a 160 bit security limit. New macOS systems use AES for arc4random, so it is safer to make the switch.

commit.message: Switch constant time comparison function to one that handles length internally. This means we don't need to use strlen(), which might leak the password length via timing. Also, eliminate uses of strlen() to warn on empty or short passphrases. Finally, make sure we zero the passphrases before exiting due to error
